h shape.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Problem Solving (50%)**: Correct answers for graphing and zeros.\n- **Concept Understanding (30%)**: Quality of your explanation notes.\n- **Use of Technology (10%)**: Screenshots or graphs included.\n- **Effort and Organization (10%)**: Work presented clearly.\n\n---\n\n### Week 3: Exponential and Logarithmic Functions\n**Topic Covered:** Exponential growth and decay, Logarithms and their properties\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Review \"3.1 Exponential Functions\", \"3.2 Logarithmic Functions and Graphs\", \"3.3 Properties of Logarithms\".\n2. Complete practice problems:\n   - Evaluate logs and exponents.\n   - Solve exponential and logarithmic equations.\n3. Model a real-life scenario showing exponential growth or decay and explain it.\n4. Prepare for a short quiz on these properties.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Accuracy (40%)**: Correct solutions for problems.\n- **Application (30%)**: Real-life model relevance and explanation.\n- **Quiz Score (20%)**: Quiz results.\n- **Clarity (10%)**: Clear explanations and work shown.\n\n---\n\n### Week 4: Trigonometry Basics\n**Topic Covered:** Radians, degrees, unit circle, right triangle trig\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Study \"4.1 Radian & Degree\", \"4.2 The Unit Circle\", and introduction to right triangle trig.\n2. Practice converting between radians and degrees.\n3. Use the unit circle to find sine, cosine, and tangent of common angles.\n4. Solve right triangle problems using trigonometric ratios.\n5. Complete a worksheet on these topics.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Completeness (40%)**: All worksheet problems attempted.\n- **Correctness (40%)**: Correct answers for trig problems.\n- **Conceptual Understanding (20%)**: Ability to explain radian-degree conversion and unit circle values.\n\n---\n\n### Week 5: Advanced Trigonometry\n**Topic Covered:** Other trig functions, graphs, inverse trig functions, applications\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Review \"4.5 Graphs of Sine and Cosine\", \"4.6 Other Trig Functions\", \"4.7 Inverse Trig Functions\", \"4.8 Applications & Models\".\n2. Sketch graphs of sine, cosine, secant, cosecant, tangent, cotangent.\n3. Solve for angles using inverse trig functions.\n4. Apply trigonometry to real-world models (e.g., pendulum motion).\n5. Prepare a mini-presentation explaining inverse trig functions.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Graph Accuracy (30%)**: Correct graphs plotted.\n- **Problem Solving (30%)**: Correct inverse trig solutions.\n- **Application Explanation (20%)**: Quality of real-world problem and explanation.\n- **Presentation (20%)**: Clear and engaging explanation in the mini-presentation.\n\n---\n\n### Week 6: Trig Identities and Equations\n**Topic Covered:** Using identities, verifying identities, solving trig equations\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Study \"5.1 Using Identities\", \"5.2 Verifying Identities\", \"5.3 Solving Trig Equations\".\n2. Complete exercises verifying basic trig identities.\n3. Solve standard trig equations.\n4. Provide explanations for each step in solving identities or equations.\n5. Submit work showing all steps clearly.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Accuracy (50%)**: Correct verification and solutions.\n- **Working shown (30%)**: Clear step-by-step explanations.\n- **Effort (20%)**: Completeness and neatness of submitted work.\n\n---\n\n### Week 7-8: Vectors and Dot Products\n**Topic Covered:** Vectors in space, vector notation, dot product, orthogonality\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Use \"10.2 Vectors in Space (Teacher)\" and \"10.2 Vectors in Space\" materials.\n2. Define zero vector, unit vectors, and write vectors in component form.\n3. Calculate magnitude of vectors and dot products.\n4. Determine angles between vectors and test for orthogonality or parallelism.\n5. Solve application problems involving forces or directions.\n6. Create a concept map linking vector properties and operations.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Problem Accuracy (50%)**: Correct vector computations.\n- **Concept Map (30%)**: Clear and accurate concept relationships.\n- **Application (20%)**: Correct application problem solutions.\n\n---\n\n### Week 9-10: Cross Product and 3D Coordinate Systems\n**Topic Covered:** Cross product of vectors, 3D coordinate geometry\n\n**Quest Instructions:**\n1. Study \"10.3 Cross Product\" and \"10.1 3-D Coordinate System\".\n2. Find cross products algebraically and geometrically.\n3. Find a unit vector orthogonal to two given vectors.\n4. Solve problems locating points and vectors in 3D.\n5. Create a diagram to demonstrate cross product direction.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**\n- **Cross Product Accuracy (50%)**: Correct algebraic and geometric answers.\n- **Diagram Quality (30%)**: Neat, correct illustration of 3D vectors.\n- **Problem Solving (20%)**: Accuracy in 3D coordinate problems.\n\n---\n\n### General Notes and Accommodations:\n- Since your interests and learning style are currently unspecified, I suggest blending visual aids (slides and graphs), written explanations, and practical applications to help with understanding.\n- Practice step-by-step to build confidence and competence.\n- Use online graphing tools or calculators as needed to visualize concepts.\n- If you want, we can customize further once you share preferences or goals.\n\n---\n\nIf you provide your learning style or interests later, I can adapt these quests further! For now, this detailed weekly quest plan with grading criteria will guide you in mastering grade 10 Pre-Calculus topics.\n\nIf you want me to prepare detailed instructions for any specific week or topic, just ask!\n\n---\n\nReferences: These instructions and rubrics are aligned with the Pre-Calc units and lessons found in your uploaded materials on vectors, trigonometry, functions, and polynomial topics."